content:
Nice puzzle. A bit too tricking in my opinion to understand that the gcd of n numbers is the gcd of previous (n-1) numbers and n, and for whenever there's a range longer than 1 it's automatically gcd one. Kudos to anyone figuring this out in a 15 minute CoC. Also in your code, if li!=ri, why do you do:
g = __gcd(g, 1LL);
and not:
g = 1LL;
?
